<item>
            <title>[NET-551] Util copyReader calls CopyStreamListener.bytesTransferred with the incorrect value for bytesTransferred</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-551</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Util copyReader calls CopyStreamListener.bytesTransferred with the incorrect value for bytesTransferred parameter if it reads a single character.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It uses the value of the field chars which at that point contains the character, rather than the number read.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code also re-uses the chars field for both the number of characters read and the single character, which is quite confusing. &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;The copyStream also re-uses the bytes field, but uses the correct bytesTransferred parameter&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
